commander.Name: Heinz Kokott
commander.PersBio:
Heinz Kokott was born November 14, 1890. He joined the German Army on October 10, 1918 and served as a Lieutenant in the infantry.
He was awarded the Iron Cross on March 17, 1943 while commanding Grenadier Regiment 337 of the 208th Infantry Division near Orel, Russia.
Kokott had the dubious honor of being brother in law to Gestapo Chief Heinrich Himmler. Shy, but scholarly and dignified, Kokott was a commander who never raised his voice and tended to be temperate in his actions and judgments.
